  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Create Comprehensive README Documentation\n\nWrite a complete README.md file that serves as the primary documentation for the project, covering all essential information for developers and users.\n\nRequirements:\n- Add a project title and brief description of what the application does\n- Document all major features with clear explanations of functionality\n- Provide step-by-step instructions for local development setup including:\n  - Prerequisites (Node.js version, package manager, dependencies)\n  - Installation commands\n  - Environment variables and configuration needed\n  - How to start the development server\n- Include testing documentation:\n  - How to run the full test suite\n  - How to run specific test types (unit, integration, e2e if applicable)\n  - Commands for test coverage reports\n- Document CMS usage:\n  - How to access the CMS interface\n  - Authentication/login process for CMS\n  - How to create, edit, and publish content\n  - Overview of content types and their purposes\n- Add sections for:\n  - Project structure overview\n  - Available scripts and their purposes\n  - Troubleshooting common issues\n- Use clear formatting with proper headings, code blocks, and examples\n- Ensure all commands are copy-pasteable and tested",
